# No Em Dashes in Explanations

When explaining topics, do not use em dashes (—) or double hyphens (--) as substitutes. Use alternative punctuation instead:

- Use commas, parentheses, colons, or semicolons
- Restructure into separate sentences when needed

Em dashes are acceptable in titles, headings, attributions, and citations.
